###########################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"answerHints.pl",

"PGML.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

###########################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");
$t = random(2, 8);
$P = random(1000, 5000, 500);
$r = random(4, 8);
$I = $P*$r*$t/100;

$rate = $r/100;
$rhs = $P*$t;



###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
Find the rate if a principal of [`$[$P]`] earned [`$[$I]`] interest in [$t] years.

[_________________]{$r} %

*Hint:  I = PRT*

END_PGML


############################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can use the formula

*I = PRT*

to solve simple interest problems.

I = interest earned,
P = principal,
R = interest rate (as a decimal),
T = time (in years)

In this problem,

I = [$I]

P = [$P]

R = ?

T = [$t]

If we plug those values into the formula, we get:

[`[$I] = [$P]\cdot x \cdot [$t]`]

[`[$I] = [$rhs]x`]

[`x = [$I] \div [$rhs] = [$rate] = [$r]`]%

END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('MathObject version. Uses PGML.');

ENDDOCUMENT();